remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` provides static methods for encoding pixel data as WebP images,
including both single-frame and animated WebP files.

Use the `Encode` overloads to encode a single <xref:SkiaSharp.SKPixmap> to a
stream or <xref:SkiaSharp.SKData>. Use the `EncodeAnimated` overloads to encode a
sequence of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> values as an animated WebP file.

This type has no state; all methods are static.

## Examples

```csharp
using var bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode("input.png");
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();

var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 80);

var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
if (data != null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("output.webp", data.ToArray());
```
